# harness.selection — pick which optional items to install.
#
# Copy this file to "harness.selection" (same directory) and edit. The bootstrap
# reads it on every run, so re-running after `git pull` keeps your selection.
# Override the path with the HARNESS_SELECTION env var, or override a single
# category for one run with a flag, e.g.  ./install.sh --skills=tdd,grill-with-docs
#
# Format:  <category> <name-or-glob> [more names ...]
#   categories: skills | subagents | commands
#   '#' starts a comment; blank lines are ignored
#   shell globs work: '*-reviewer', 'springboot-*', etc.
#
# IMPORTANT: a category with NO lines here installs EVERYTHING in that category.
# So an empty or absent file = install all (the default behavior). Rules are NOT
# selectable — they are centralized and always installed in full.

# --- skills (bundle + vendored; matched by skill directory name) ------------
# skills tdd grill-with-docs
# skills springboot-* nextjs-turbopack
# skills diagnose triage

# --- subagents (reviewer/resolver personas; matched by file name, no .md) ----
# subagents nextjs-reviewer spring-reviewer sql-reviewer
# subagents *-reviewer

# --- commands (slash commands / prompts; matched by file name, no .md) -------
# commands review-pr
